 "draftNote": "1 of five queued off a bottom-two lane: Mr_Meat31 (midlane→offlane).",
 "coaching": {
  "headline": "A 30-minute objective stranglehold — every Fangtooth, Prime, and Orb was yours, towers 10-3, +22 VP.",
  "team": "This wasn't a fight win, it was a map win: you took the neutrals 24-14 and snowballed it into a 10-3 tower lead. Cuban's Sparrow gave you the carry to cash those leads in (16/1/1), and your anti-heal was on point — four Tainted items buried their Riktor at 0/5/6 so their one healer never mattered. The lever is that this was a clean five-stack executing the right win condition: keep playing for objectives off won fights instead of chasing kills.",
  "whatShiftedIt": "Even in a win, build the resist your matchup demands — Xeebs' Khaimera ran zero magic resist into a 3-magical enemy comp, and against a sharper team that's a free death window.",
  "perPlayer": {
   "a0c393cc-1437-4bdc-8168-64676ce2166c": "Sparrow hard-carried at 16/1/1 — yours at every checkpoint vs Revenant, one death all game and 35k hero damage. Even with your Vanquisher spike not landing until ~25m, the lane was won outright before then; this win keyed off you.",
   "a412baf3-dd17-4f89-8ecf-9d0704f3a79e": "Khaimera jungle, 7/5/12 — yours at every checkpoint vs Boris on your comfort pick. You won it on play; just buy magic resist into their 3-magical comp next time, because that's the one thing that could have opened a death window in the late fights.",
   "16f28434-561f-4f23-9454-40321f4a1ef3": "Iggy & Scorch, 4/1/7 and 40k into objectives — even early then yours from 15 minutes on vs Aurora, and your Wraith Leggings spike ~25m lined up with that takeover. Your zone control is exactly why every neutral fell your way.",
   "7c8ab99c-31c5-4ea5-a6fa-e0d6417c3f1b": "The Fey mid, 2/1/14 with a single death — the Gadget lane was even early and tipped yours from ~20 minutes on, right around your Wraith Leggings spike (~19m). Your peel and 14 assists let the carry farm kills safely.",
   "10edbf65-457d-48d0-9151-9df5b4fcb40a": "Steel support, 0/4/19 — even early then yours from 15 minutes on vs Riktor, eating 46k damage and mitigating 48k as the frontline. Pure enabling, and your Tainted item helped shut their Riktor down."
  }
 },
